r followed by a \\\"Mike's Groove\\\" that included\"},{\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/www.jambands.com\\/news\\/2015\\/06\\/26\\/kung-fu-drummer-plays-with-pink-talking-fish\",\"id\":\"f22f2adc912aaf3d155b51380b427a0c\",\"date_found\":\"2015-06-27T00:00:00\",\"name\":\"Kung Fu Drummer Plays with Pink Talking Fish\",\"summary\":\"Last night in Pittston, PA, Pink Talking Fish welcomed out Kung Fu drummer Adrian Tramontano for the entire two set show at the Northeast Fair. Among the tunes played were an opening \\\"2001\\\" jam as well as Phish tunes \\\"Wilson\\\" and \\\"Run Like an Antelope.\\\" <span>The Pink Floyd<\\/span> catalog was also well-represented with takes on \\\"Have a Cigar,\\\" \\\"Young Lust,\\\" \\\"Wish You Were Here,\\\" \\\"Another Brick in the Wall\\\" and others. As always, PTF shared a fair amount of Talking Heads material. Among them, \\\"Life During Wartime,\\\" \\\"Burning Down the House,\\\" \\\"Crosseyed and Painless\\\" and more. Next up for Pink Talking Fish is a Mike\"},{\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/www.antimusic.com\\/news\\/15\\/June\\/25Pink_Floyd,_King_Crimson_Lead_Progressive_Music_Awards_Nominations.shtml\",\"id\":\"7f18b6a3335bd484e87fcf982a3c6ad9\",\"date_found\":\"2015-06-25T00:00:00\",\"name\":\"Pink Floyd, King Crimson Lead Progressive Music Awards Nominations\",\"summary\":\"Awards. The 2015 awards will again take place at London's Underglobe venue, beneath Shakepseare's Globe Theatre, on Thursday September 3. This year, the event will be hosted of the first time by TV presenter Matthew Wright. You can vote for your choice of the nominees at: progmagazine.com\\/awards. <span>Pink Floyd<\\/span>'s The Endless River album sees them pick up three nominations for Grand Design, Album and Band\\/Artist of the Year. King Crimson and Steven Wilson are the only other artists with three nominations and go head-to-head in the Grand Design category. Wilson is also nominated for Band\\/Artist of the ... Steve Hillage for the first time. I spent a lot of time listening to his Green album and his stuff with Gong but I never thought I'd meet him. I also met Robert John Godfrey, who I'd seen live many times but had never met before. The experience was only marred by the fact I had to get up at 4am the next morning to do my show, so I think I might take the Friday off this time!\\\" See the full nomination list here. Classic Rock Magazine is an official news provider for antiMusic.com. Copyright Classic Rock Magazine- Excerpted here with permission. <span>Pink Floyd<\\/span>, King Crimson Lead Progressive Music Awards Nominations\"},{\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/www.billboard.com\\/articles\\/news\\/dance\\/6605919\\/nicolas-jaar-drops-surprise-album-pomegranates\",\"id\":\"58f1407ae376ea8ee3bc513dff4daa17\",\"date_found\":\"2015-06-25T00:00:00\",\"name\":\"Nicolas Jaar Drops Surprise Album 'Pomegranates'\",\"summary\":\"meandering and memorable debut Space is Only Noise in 2011, the Chilean-American talent has managed to avoid putting out a solo successor.Indie Beat: Nicolas Jaar on Building a Label for Digital Natives His DARKSIDE project with Dave Harrington was a different (yet just as worthwhile) beast that channeled <span>Pink Floyd<\\/span> in its majestic rock-oriented arrangements. The release of Jaar's third EP Nymphs II in May followed the revelation that he had composed a soundtrack to a 1969 Soviet art film called The Colour of Pomegranates. Now that soundtrack has surfaced in the form of a second standalone album titled\"},{\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/www.virginmedia.com\\/music\\/news\\/story\\/2015\\/06\\/25\\/pink-floyd-up-for-three\\/\",\"id\":\"93f95aac334de2d061d0f4b8e8c2ffb9\",\"date_found\":\"2015-06-25T00:00:00\",\"name\":\"Pink Floyd up for three Progressive Music Awards\",\"summary\":\"<span>Pink Floyd<\\/span>'s Nick Mason <span>Pink Floyd<\\/span> have been nominated for three awards at the 2015 Progressive Music Awards. The legendary rock band's chart-topping 'The Endless River' LP sees them up for the Grand Design, Best Album and Best Band\\/Artist of the Year prizes. <span>Pink Floyd<\\/span> - Dave Gilmour and Nick Mason - are joined on three nominations by King Crimson and Steven Wilson. Meanwhile, Kate Bush is up for two awards, Best Live Event and Artist of the Year, following her return to the stage in 2014, her first live shows in 35 years. The 4th Annual Progressive Music Awards - created by Prog Magazine - will take ... Summer Now (from Scorch) Vennart - Operate (from The Demon Joke) Von Hertzen Brothers - Hold Me Up (from New Day Rising) Album of the Year: Amplifier - Mystoria Beardfish - +4626 comfortzone Flying Colors - Second Nature Nightwish - Endless Forms Most Beautiful Opeth - Pale Communion <span>Pink Floyd<\\/span> - The Endless River Periphery - Juggernaut Steven Wilson - Hand.Cannot.Erase. Sweet Billy Pilgrim - Motorcade Amnesiacs The Pineapple Thief - Magnolia Band\\/Artist of the Year: Between The Buried & Me Flying Colors Kate Bush King Crimson Opeth <span>Pink Floyd<\\/span> Steve Hackett Steven Wilson Threshold Von Hertzen Brothers\"},{\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/www.jambase.com\\/Articles\\/125559\\/RecommNeds-Truls-Morck-and-Les-Big-Byrd\",\"id\":\"42cb5d3a2eb6ed60248dbbd70e290568\",\"date_found\":\"2015-06-25T00:00:00\",\"name\":\"RecommNeds | Truls Morck & Les Big Byrd\",\"summary\":\"the next couple weeks with moreextended stays in some overseas locales. This week brings us two bands from Sweden. Truls M\\u00f6rck: Truls M\\u00f6rck Truls M\\u00f6rck is an on-again\\/off-again member of heavy metal band Graveyard, buthis solo, self-titled debut album is another kind of 1970s throwback, with <span>Pink Floyd<\\/span> space-outs in an almost Laurel Canyon setting. With excellent songs and a laid-back, let-loosegroove, M\\u00f6rck comes off like a Swedish Jonathan Wilson, which is to say the album is quitegood: interstellar guitars and pre-disco electric piano and organ. It's a slow burner that'sworth a little\"},{\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/www.virginmedia.com\\/music\\/news\\/story\\/2015\\/06\\/19\\/roger-waters-told-to-hoot\\/\",\"id\":\"f216e50fab4356086b35e420c097e66b\",\"date_found\":\"2015-06-20T00:00:00\",\"name\":\"Roger Waters told to 'shoot himself'\",\"summary\":\"Roger Waters Roger Waters was told to ''shoot himself'' by his school teacher as a child. <span>The Pink Floyd<\\/span> musician revealed his tutor confronted him in class as a youngster and told him he would never do anything valuable with his life because he was ''useless''. He recalled: ''I've had some measure of success and there's no question that it provides one with something of a bulwark against T.E House who was the a*shole at my grammar school who told me I was a complete f**king idiot. ''He was an English teacher and he was my form master when I was 13. ''He said I would never become anything and might as well\"},{\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/music-news.com\\/shownews.asp?H=Ed-Sheeran,-Sam-Smith-and-George-Ezra-driving-British-male-success&nItemID=90082\",\"id\":\"b118b34e11f521936a8c6882c3fe4319\",\"date_found\":\"2015-06-15T00:00:00\",\"name\":\"Ed Sheeran, Sam Smith and George Ezra driving British male success\",\"summary\":\"with Paolo Nutini and Olly Murs also performing strongly. It's a trend underlined by the recent successes of James Bay (2015), Sam Smith (2014) and Tom Odell (2013) in claiming the BRITs Critics' Choice Award following five years of Female Artist dominance. Male Groups, which last year included iconic Rock act <span>Pink Floyd<\\/span>, nevertheless accounted for a further four titles in the top 10 and also claimed over a third of sales in 2014. When each gender group's sales are analysed by nationality the UK achieved its strongest sales share (63.4 per cent) in the Male Group category and its weakest (39.3 per cent) ... Coldplay Ghost Stories Parlophone\\/Parlophone (Warner Music UK) 6. Paloma Faith A Perfect Contradiction RCA\\/RCA Label Group (Sony Music Entertainment UK) 7. One Direction Four Syco Music\\/S