mour revealed that he plans to hit the road on this side of the pond next year. Gilmour also shared a few more pieces of information during his appearance at the festival, including the name of his highly anticipated solo album, and performed\"},{\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/www.billboard.com\\/articles\\/news\\/6590831\\/emmylou-harris-and-dame-evelyn-glennie-honored-with-swedens-polar-music-prize\",\"id\":\"f7de379f68e91fe4212f7a66a37f5f87\",\"date_found\":\"2015-06-10T00:00:00\",\"name\":\"Emmylou Harris and Dame Evelyn Glennie Honored with Sweden's Polar Music Prize\",\"summary\":\"many of ABBA's early hits. The prize was first presented in 1992. Anderson died in 1997; his family has taken up the mantle. The long list of previous Laureates includes Paul McCartney, Elton John, B.B. King, Joni Mitchell, Ren\\u00e9e Fleming, Stevie Wonder, Ennio Morricone, Bob Dylan, <span>Pink Floyd<\\/span>, Isaac Stern, Bj\\u00f6rk, Led Zeppelin, Miriam Makeba, Patti Smith, Yo-Yo Ma, Ravi Shankar, Quincy Jones, Dizzy Gillespie, Burt Bacharach and Bruce Springsteen. Springsteen and his wife, Patti Scialfa, sent a video message to Harris: Emmylou Harris and Dame Evelyn Glennie Honored with Sweden's Polar Music Prize\"},{\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/www.jambands.com\\/news\\/2015\\/06\\/08\\/pink-talking-fish-to-play-animals-and-gamehendge-during-halloween-run\",\"id\":\"42ba649ca53364962a27b28fc0afbe22\",\"date_found\":\"2015-06-09T00:00:00\",\"name\":\"Pink Talking Fish to Play Animals and Gamehendge During Halloween Run\",\"summary\":\"Pink Talking Fish's two-night run at The Middle East in Cambridge, MA will see the band deliver a pair of unique performances as they will take on <span>Pink Floyd<\\/span>'s Animals on October 30 along with \\\"various animal oriented themes included in the song catalogues of <span>Pink Floyd<\\/span>, the Talking Heads and Phish.\\\" Halloween night will be Gamehendge-themed. The band will perform the well-known Trey Anastasio rock opera along with material from the Talking Heads and <span>Floyd<\\/span>. The Middle East will be transformed into a jungle over the two nights and attendees are encouraged to dress up as creatures of the wild. All\"},{\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/www.antimusic.com\\/news\\/15\\/June\\/09Muse_Discuss_New_Concept_Album_Drones_.shtml\",\"id\":\"eb35b48cfa4d4b5b878410697647b8ee\",\"date_found\":\"2015-06-09T00:00:00\",\"name\":\"Muse Discuss New Concept Album 'Drones'\",\"summary\":\"becomes brainwashed by the military thereby becoming a drone, but eventually fights to free himself from the mental shackles in songs like \\\"Revolt\\\" and \\\"Defector.\\\" The album comes to a head with the whopping 10-minute track \\\"Globalist,\\\" about a dictator who starts World War III as a means to find love. When compared to <span>Pink Floyd<\\/span>'s The Wall, Howard smiles and admits, \\\"I suppose the album is a bit of a concept album, yeah. It's probably the most conceptual album that we've done.\\\" The band has tried their hand at weaving story lines though a few tracks here or there, but as for Drones Howard says, \\\"It has a narrative,\"},{\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/music-news.com\\/shownews.asp?H=Roger-Waters-The-Wall-comes-to-cinemas&nItemID=89954\",\"id\":\"d80d8ba398b82047d2372612d9f144e8\",\"date_found\":\"2015-06-09T00:00:00\",\"name\":\"Roger Waters The Wall comes to cinemas\",\"summary\":\"Printable version Roger Waters, the creative genius behind musical pioneers <span>Pink Floyd<\\/span>, in association with Picturehouse Entertainment and Fathom Events, is set to bring his groundbreaking masterpiece, Roger Waters The Wall, to cinemas across the globe on Tuesday September 29. The release will hit screens across the globe at 8pm local time. Tickets go on sale on Friday 19 June and are available at www.rogerwatersthewall.com. 'The Wall Live' - the biggest worldwide tour by any solo artist in history - now comes to cinemas as a groundbreaking concert film, written and directed by Roger Waters and Sean Evans. Described by critics as \\\"nothing short of breath-taking\\\" and \\\"visually magnificent,\\\" Roger Waters The Wall had its premiere at last year's Toronto Film Festival. The film unfolds on many levels ' as an immersive concert experience of the classic <span>Pink Floyd<\\/span> album, a road movie of Waters' reckoning with the past and as a stirring anti-war film, highlighting the human cost of conflict. The event on Tuesday September 29 also features The Simple Facts; an exclusive in-conversation with Roger Waters and Nick Mason, where <span>the Pink Floyd<\\/span> rhythm section will reunite over the breaking\"}],\"id\":\"ARD4C1I1187FB4B0C3\",\"artist_location\":{\"city\":\"London\",\"region\":'NULL',\"location\":\"London, UK\",\"country\":\"United Kingdom\"},\"discovery\":0.28693556254085}",
